        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add live provider model catalog helper",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `openclaw/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-live-runtime`, a public SDK route for provider plugins that can discover live model catalogs from a provider `/models` API.\n- Route bundled providers with live model-list APIs through that SDK path: OpenCode Go, OpenAI, xAI, Chutes, Venice, DeepInfra, Vercel AI Gateway, and NVIDIA.\n- Keep provider-owned static rows as metadata and offline fallback for capabilities, pricing, media limits, endpoint family, and configured rows.\n- Fix `models list --all --provider ...` so provider runtime catalog hooks are tried before stale static manifest rows when the provider has a live runtime catalog.\n- Update plugin-builder docs, SDK subpath docs, package exports, API metadata, and the SDK API baseline hash.\n\n## How it works\nProvider plugins keep static catalog rows as canonical metadata and fallback. A provider with a model-list API can call `buildLiveModelProviderConfig(...)` for OpenAI-style model IDs, or `getCachedLiveProviderModelRows(...)` / `fetchLiveProviderModelRows(...)` when it needs to project richer API rows into OpenClaw model definitions.\n\nThe SDK helper performs an SSRF-guarded fetch, composes caller abort signals with a bounded timeout, builds provider/discovery auth headers, parses OpenAI-style `{ data: [...] }` and top-level array bodies by default, releases guarded fetch resources, caches successful live rows by provider/endpoint/credential with a bounded process-local TTL cache, throws structured `LiveModelCatalogHttpError` for HTTP fallback handling, and falls back to provider-owned static rows when live discovery is unavailable.\n\nOpenAI stays scoped to the `openai` provider id; Azure hook aliases remain hook aliases only. OpenCode Go is marked runtime-discovered so model browsing loads the plugin runtime instead of stopping at the stale two-row manifest catalog. xAI OAuth discovery uses the Grok CLI proxy `/v1/models` endpoint. Chutes preserves its bounded token/fallback cache while using the SDK fetch route. DeepInfra, Venice, Vercel AI Gateway, NVIDIA, and OpenCode Go share the guarded live-model fetch path while retaining provider-specific parsing.\n\n## Maintainer decision surface\nLanding this PR intentionally publishes the new `openclaw/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-live-runtime` subpath as a plugin SDK contract and intentionally lets authenticated live catalogs win over static rows for provider-filtered model listing when a provider has a runtime catalog hook. Static fallback remains available when live discovery is unavailable.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openai/openai-provider.test.ts extensions/xai/index.test.ts extensions/opencode-go/index.test.ts src/commands/models/list.provider-catalog.test.ts src/commands/models/list.source-plan.test.ts src/commands/models/list.list-command.forward-compat.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-auth-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-live-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-shared.test.ts extensions/deepinfra/provider-models.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.integration.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `corepack pnpm run lint:tmp:no-raw-channel-fetch`\n- `git diff --check upstream/main..HEAD`\n- `corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider openai --json`\n- `corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider xai --json`\n- `corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider opencode-go --json`\n- Live endpoint smoke against PR head `8221079caf2bfc05e34e2f6f889d82b1ee5a2e70` for OpenAI OAuth, xAI OAuth, and OpenCode Go auth, using the PR checkout's provider catalog mappers for the model-list calls. Credential values, account/profile IDs, local paths, and process details are redacted.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: provider plugins now have a reusable SDK route for live model discovery, bundled providers with model-list APIs use it, and user-facing `models list` reaches runtime catalog hooks instead of stopping at stale static manifest rows.\n\nReal environment tested:\n- Local OpenClaw checkout on PR head `8221079caf2bfc05e34e2f6f889d82b1ee5a2e70`.\n- Crabbox AWS Linux smoke on earlier PR head `fc7007e82b983bbdbc77818ef877eb767b8a3ac7`, run `run_4d0150612794`, for public unauthenticated live providers.\n- Local authenticated provider smoke with local auth profiles or existing runtime OAuth credentials. OpenCode Go uses API-key/token auth; OpenAI and xAI use OAuth-style local auth.\n\nSanitization applied before posting: token values, bearer headers, account IDs, auth profile IDs, email/account text, local filesystem paths, raw machine targets, and process identifiers are omitted or redacted. Logs preserve provider names, endpoint URLs, HTTP statuses or command exit status, durations, returned counts, auth modes, and model IDs.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openai/openai-provider.test.ts extensions/xai/index.test.ts extensions/opencode-go/index.test.ts src/commands/models/list.provider-catalog.test.ts src/commands/models/list.source-plan.test.ts src/commands/models/list.list-command.forward-compat.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-auth-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-live-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-catalog-shared.test.ts extensions/deepinfra/provider-models.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.integration.test.ts\ncorepack pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check\ncorepack pnpm run lint:tmp:no-raw-channel-fetch\ngit diff --check upstream/main..HEAD\ncorepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider openai --json\ncorepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider xai --json\ncorepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider opencode-go --json\npnpm exec tsx <<'TS'\n# resolve local OpenAI OAuth, xAI OAuth, and OpenCode Go credentials; values redacted\n# call PR checkout provider catalog builders with a logging fetch guard\n# log sanitized endpoint, auth mode, HTTP status, duration, row count, mapped ids, and composer presence\nTS\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```json\n{\n  \"head\": \"8221079caf2bfc05e34e2f6f889d82b1ee5a2e70\",\n  \"focusedVerification\": [\n    { \"command\": \"node scripts/run-vitest.mjs <focused model catalog files>\", \"exitCode\": 0 },\n    { \"command\": \"corepack pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check\", \"exitCode\": 0, \"result\": \"OK docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\" },\n    { \"command\": \"corepack pnpm run lint:tmp:no-raw-channel-fetch\", \"exitCode\": 0 },\n    { \"command\": \"git diff --check upstream/main..HEAD\", \"exitCode\": 0 }\n  ],\n  \"cliModelList\": [\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"openai\",\n      \"command\": \"corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider openai --json\",\n      \"exitCode\": 0,\n      \"count\": 3,\n      \"available\": 0,\n      \"keys\": [\"openai/gpt-5.4\", \"openai/gpt-5.4-mini\", \"openai/gpt-5.5\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"xai\",\n      \"command\": \"corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider xai --json\",\n      \"exitCode\": 0,\n      \"count\": 5,\n      \"available\": 0,\n      \"keys\": [\n        \"xai/grok-4.20-beta-latest-non-reasoning\",\n        \"xai/grok-4.20-beta-latest-reasoning\",\n        \"xai/grok-4.3\",\n        \"xai/grok-build-0.1\",\n        \"xai/grok-composer-2.5-fast\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"opencode-go\",\n      \"command\": \"corepack pnpm openclaw models list --all --provider opencode-go --json\",\n      \"exitCode\": 0,\n      \"count\": 18,\n      \"available\": 18,\n      \"keys\": [\n        \"opencode-go/deepseek-v4-flash\",\n        \"opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro\",\n        \"opencode-go/glm-5\",\n        \"opencode-go/glm-5.1\",\n        \"opencode-go/hy3-preview\",\n        \"opencode-go/kimi-k2.5\",\n        \"opencode-go/kimi-k2.6\",\n        \"opencode-go/mimo-v2-omni\",\n        \"opencode-go/mimo-v2-pro\",\n        \"opencode-go/mimo-v2.5\",\n        \"opencode-go/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n        \"opencode-go/minimax-m2.5\",\n        \"opencode-go/minimax-m2.7\",\n        \"opencode-go/minimax-m3\",\n        \"opencode-go/qwen3.5-plus\",\n        \"opencode-go/qwen3.6-plus\",\n        \"opencode-go/qwen3.7-max\",\n        \"opencode-go/qwen3.7-plus\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"liveEndpointCatalog\": [\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"openai\",\n      \"testedCode\": \"PR checkout extensions/openai/openai-provider.ts\",\n      \"auth\": \"oauth\",\n      \"profileId\": \"<redacted>\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex/models?client_version=1.0.0\",\n      \"httpStatus\": 200,\n      \"durationMs\": 329,\n      \"bodyShape\": \"{models:[]}\",\n      \"rawRows\": 5,\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-chatgpt-responses\",\n      \"mappedCount\": 4,\n      \"ids\": [\"gpt-5.5\", \"gpt-5.4\", \"gpt-5.4-mini\", \"gpt-5.3-codex-spark\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"xai\",\n      \"testedCode\": \"PR checkout extensions/xai/provider-catalog.ts\",\n      \"auth\": \"oauth\",\n      \"profileId\": \"<redacted>\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"https://cli-chat-proxy.grok.com/v1/models\",\n      \"httpStatus\": 200,\n      \"durationMs\": 195,\n      \"bodyShape\": \"{data:[]}\",\n      \"rawRows\": 2,\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://cli-chat-proxy.grok.com/v1\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-responses\",\n      \"mappedCount\": 2,\n      \"ids\": [\"grok-composer-2.5-fast\", \"grok-build\"],\n      \"hasComposer25\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"provider\": \"opencode-go\",\n      \"testedCode\": \"PR checkout extensions/opencode-go/provider-catalog.ts\",\n      \"auth\": \"api-key\",\n      \"profileId\": \"<redacted>\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/models\",\n      \"httpStatus\": 200,\n      \"durationMs\": 198,\n      \"bodyShape\": \"{data:[]}\",\n      \"rawRows\": 18,\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1\",\n      \"api\": \"o